cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses a neural network architecture that combines classification and reconstruction, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The addition of a "style memory" to the output layer is a unique contribution, which could also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the relationship between style memory and composing digits and letters, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
